&nbsp;

Coco can only replace parts of the ESIM db as CAPRI is not a world model and does not include all the regions (in particular the US and ROW) as ESIM. As the COCO data preparation is quite complex and data intensive, extending COCO to the other regions does not seem feasible given time and data constraints. Thus, only parts of the ESIM db will be replaced by coco data as available. This makes differing definitions between ESIM and COCO particularly problematic since any definition taken over from COCO would require to adapt products also for the regions not available in COCO.

Is a database harmonization only possible for the smallest common denominator, i.e. where countries and definitions are identical?

Other problematic area: mapping of prices: margins are taken from older ESIM database =&gt; difficult to change definitions because then margins don't fit any more.

