The goal is to generate a theoretically consistent set of income and price elasticities of demand for a Linear Expenditure System, given a set of income and own price elasticities ($$&#92;eta_i$$ and $$&#92;epsilon_{ii}$$), the budget ($$M$$) and vectors of prices and quantities demanded ($$p_i$$ and $$q_i$$).

The corresponding optimization model with a maximum entropy objective is the following:

From maximizing the utility subject to the budget constraint the LES demand function is derived:

$$&#92;max H(&#92;pi) = -&#92;sum_{i &#92;in I} &#92;sum_{l &#92;in L} &#92;pi_{il}^&#92;eta &#92;ln &#92;pi_{il}^&#92;eta -&#92;sum_{i &#92;in I} &#92;sum_{l &#92;in L} &#92;pi_{il}^&#92;epsilon &#92;ln &#92;pi_{il}^&#92;epsilon$$

subject to

$$ &#92;begin{array}{rlll} 
&#92;eta_i &amp;= &#92;sum_{l &#92;in L} &#92;pi_{il}^&#92;eta z_{il}^&#92;eta &#92;qquad &amp;&#92;forall i &#92;in I &amp;&#92;text{($&#92;eta$ to ME link)}&#92;&#92;
&#92;epsilon_{ii} &amp;= &#92;sum_{l &#92;in L} &#92;pi_{il}^&#92;epsilon z_{il}^&#92;epsilon &#92;qquad &amp;&#92;forall i &#92;in I &amp;&#92;text{($&#92;epsilon$ to ME link)}&#92;&#92;
&#92;sum_{l &#92;in L} &#92;pi_{il}^&#92;eta &amp;= 1 &#92;qquad &amp;&#92;forall i &#92;in I &amp;&#92;text{(Support point probabilities for each product add up to one)}&#92;&#92;
&#92;sum_{l &#92;in L} &#92;pi_{il}^&#92;epsilon &amp;= 1 &#92;qquad &amp;&#92;forall i &#92;in I &amp;&#92;text{(Support point probabilities for each product add up to one)}&#92;&#92;
p_i q_i &amp;= p_i &#92;gamma_i + &#92;beta_i (M - &#92;sum_j p_j &#92;gamma_j) &amp;&#92;forall i &#92;in I &amp;&#92;text{(LES demand function)}&#92;&#92;
&#92;eta_i &amp;= &#92;frac{&#92;beta_i}{w_i} = &#92;beta_i &#92;frac{&#92;sum_{j &#92;in I} p_j q_j}{p_i q_i} &amp;&#92;forall i &#92;in I  &amp;&#92;text{(Income elasticity)}&#92;&#92;
&#92;epsilon_{ii} &amp;= -1 + (1-&#92;beta_i)&#92;frac{&#92;gamma_i}{q_i} &amp;&#92;forall i &#92;in I  &amp;&#92;text{(Own price elasticity)}&#92;&#92;
&#92;sum_{i &#92;in I} &#92;beta_i &amp;= 1 &amp; &amp;&#92;text{(Adding up restriction)}&#92;&#92;
&#92;end{array}$$

and the domains:

$$&#92;beta_i &#92;ge 1$$

$$0 &#92;le &#92;gamma_i &#92;le q_i$$

$$&#92;pi_{il}^&#92;eta &#92;ge 0, &#92;pi_{il}^&#92;epsilon &#92;ge 0$$

where

$$&#92;pi_{il}$$: probability for support point l of product i,

$$z_{il}$$: support point l for product i,

$$I, L$$: set of product and support points, respectively.

The support points $$z_{il}$$ are chosen so that the link function yields the exogenously given elasticity, i.e., if a support space of $$|L|=5$$ points is chosen, then the elasticity value is used as the mid point of the 5 points and the remaining points are chosen symmetrically around that point. For example, if the the income elasticity $$&#92;eta_i=1.2$$ then $$z_i^&#92;eta = (0.2,0.7,1.2,1.7,2.2)$$ and the initial corresponding probability vector takes the uniform distribution, i.e., $$&#92;pi_i^&#92;eta = (1/5,1/5,1/5,1/5,1/5)$$.

The goal is to generate a theoretically consistent set of income and price elasticities of demand for a Linear Expenditure System, given a set of income and own price elasticities ($$&#92;eta_i$$ and $$&#92;epsilon_{ii}$$), the budget ($$M$$) and vectors of prices and quantities demanded ($$p_i$$ and $$q_i$$).

The corresponding optimization model with a maximum entropy objective is the following:

From maximizing the utility subject to the budget constraint the LES demand function is derived:

$$ &#92;begin{array}{rl} 
&#92;max H(&#92;pi) =&amp; -&#92;sum_{i &#92;in &#92;{I&#92;setminus i_{nf}&#92;}} &#92;sum_{l &#92;in L} &#92;pi_{il}^&#92;eta &#92;ln &#92;pi_{il}^&#92;eta -&#92;sum_{i &#92;in I} &#92;sum_{l &#92;in L} &#92;pi_{il}^&#92;epsilon &#92;ln &#92;pi_{il}^&#92;epsilon&#92;&#92;&amp; -&#92;sum_{i &#92;in I} &#92;sum_{l &#92;in L} &#92;pi_{il}^{&#92;omega^&#92;eta} &#92;ln &#92;pi_{il}^{&#92;omega^&#92;eta} -&#92;sum_{i &#92;in I} &#92;sum_{l &#92;in L} &#92;pi_{il}^{&#92;omega^&#92;epsilon} &#92;ln &#92;pi_{il}^{&#92;omega^&#92;epsilon}
&#92;end{array}$$

subject to

$$ &#92;begin{array}{rlll} 
p_i q_i &amp;= p_i &#92;gamma_i + &#92;beta_i (M - &#92;sum_j p_j &#92;gamma_j) &amp;&#92;forall i &#92;in I &amp;&#92;text{(LES demand function)}&#92;&#92;
&#92;eta_i &amp;= &#92;frac{&#92;beta_i}{w_i} = &#92;beta_i &#92;frac{&#92;sum_{j &#92;in I} p_j q_j}{p_i q_i} + &#92;omega_i^{&#92;eta} &amp;&#92;forall i &#92;in I  &amp;&#92;text{(Income elasticity)}&#92;&#92;
&#92;epsilon_{ii} &amp;= -1 + (1-&#92;beta_i)&#92;frac{&#92;gamma_i}{q_i} + &#92;omega_i^{&#92;epsilon} &amp;&#92;forall i &#92;in I  &amp;&#92;text{(Own price elasticity)}&#92;&#92;
&#92;sum_{i &#92;in I} &#92;beta_i &amp;= 1 &amp; &amp;&#92;text{(Adding up restriction)}&#92;&#92;
&#92;eta_i &amp;= &#92;sum_{l &#92;in L} &#92;pi_{il}^&#92;eta z_{il}^&#92;eta, &#92;hspace{7pt} &amp;&#92;forall i &#92;in I &amp;&#92;text{($&#92;eta$ to ME link)}&#92;&#92;
&#92;epsilon_{ii} &amp;= &#92;sum_{l &#92;in L} &#92;pi_{il}^&#92;epsilon z_{il}^&#92;epsilon &amp;&#92;forall i &#92;in &#92;{I&#92;setminus i_{nf}&#92;} &amp;&#92;text{($&#92;epsilon$ to ME link)}&#92;&#92;
&#92;omega_i^{&#92;eta} &amp;= &#92;sum_{l &#92;in L} &#92;pi_{il}^{&#92;omega^{&#92;eta}} z_{il}^{&#92;omega^{&#92;eta}}, &#92;hspace{7pt} &#92;omega_i^{&#92;epsilon_{ii}} = &#92;sum_{l &#92;in L} &#92;pi_{il}^{&#92;omega^&#92;epsilon} z_{il}^{&#92;omega^&#92;epsilon} &amp;&#92;forall i &#92;in I &amp;&#92;text{(error to ME links)}&#92;&#92;
&#92;sum_{l &#92;in L} &#92;pi_{il}^&#92;eta &amp;= 1  ,  &#92;hspace{7pt} &#92;sum_{l &#92;in L} &#92;pi_{il}^&#92;epsilon = 1 &#92;qquad &amp;&#92;forall i &#92;in I &amp;&#92;text{(Support point probabilities add up to one)}&#92;&#92;
&#92;sum_{l &#92;in L} &#92;pi_{il}^{&#92;omega^&#92;eta} &amp;= 1  ,  &#92;hspace{7pt} &#92;sum_{l &#92;in L} &#92;pi_{il}^{&#92;omega^&#92;epsilon} = 1 &#92;qquad &amp;&#92;forall i &#92;in I &amp;&#92;text{(Error support point probabilities add up to one)}&#92;&#92;
&#92;end{array}$$

and the domains:<br />
$$0 &#92;le &#92;beta_i &#92;le 1$$, $$0 &#92;le &#92;gamma_i &#92;le q_i$$,<br />
$$&#92;pi_{il}^&#92;eta &#92;ge 0, &#92;pi_{il}^&#92;epsilon &#92;ge 0, &#92;pi_{il}^{&#92;omega^&#92;eta} &#92;ge 0, &#92;pi_{il}^{&#92;omega^&#92;epsilon} &#92;ge 0$$<br />
$$&#92;pi_{i_{nf}l}^{&#92;omega^&#92;epsilon} = 0$$<br />
where<br />
$$&#92;pi_{il}$$: probability for support point l of product i,<br />
$$z_{il}$$: support point l for product i,<br />
$$I, L$$: set of product and support points, respectively.

The support points $$z_{il}$$ are chosen so that the link function yields the exogenously given elasticity, i.e., if a support space of $$|L|=5$$ points is chosen, then the elasticity value is used as the mid point of the 5 points and the remaining points are chosen symmetrically around that point. For example, if the the income elasticity $$&#92;eta_i=1.2$$ then $$z_i^&#92;eta = (0.2,0.7,1.2,1.7,2.2)$$ and the initial corresponding probability vector takes the uniform distribution, i.e., $$&#92;pi_i^&#92;eta = (1/5,1/5,1/5,1/5,1/5)$$.
